.TH "snd_pcm_new_stream" 9 "snd_pcm_new_stream" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_new_stream \- create a new PCM stream
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_pcm_new_stream
.BI "(struct snd_pcm *pcm "  ","
.BI "int stream "  ","
.BI "int substream_count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcm" 12
the pcm instance
.IP "stream" 12
the stream direction, SNDRV_PCM_STREAM_XXX
.IP "substream_count" 12
the number of substreams
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a new stream for the pcm.
The corresponding stream on the pcm must have been empty before
calling this, i.e. zero must be given to the argument of
\fBsnd_pcm_new\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
